 I'm settling on Integration as the primary level for both, with Unit as a lower-confidence alternative: behavior 2 gets 0.15 Unit / 0.80 Integration / 0.05 System, and behavior 4 gets 0.25 Unit / 0.70 Integration / 0.05 System. These distributions reflect that while careful mocking might work in theory, real files offer the practical reliability needed to catch genuine failures.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13408,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13408},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f90286e5-583a-4db4-b303-bfdfee0f3e00","uuid":"4ee79f43-bc65-4924-a6c4-b483e593a65b"}
